-- Booker-Nominated Novelist Beryl Bainbridge Dies at Age of 75
-- Chris Spillane
-- 2010-07-02T11:55:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-02/beryl-bainbridge-booker-prize-nominated-u-k-novelist-dies-at-age-of-75.html

          
          
             British novelist  Beryl Bainbridge ,
who was nominated five times for the Booker Prize, has died at
the age of 75.  
 Bainbridge, whose works included The Dressmaker and Injury
Time, also won the Whitbread novel award twice. She published
her first novel, A Weekend with Claude, in 1967.  
 The writer passed away in the early hours of this morning
following a recurrence of a long-term illness, Anna Power, an
agent for Johnson & Alcock, said today in a phone interview.
“Beryl was taken into hospital a few days ago and now her
family is preparing a statement,” she said.  
